				\begin{document}$${F}_{max}^{i}$$\end{document}Fmaxi values calculated by each GPU thread i is stored in global memory (Fig. 12). The maximum value Fmax across all these threads can be calculated using parallel reduction, directly in global memory. However, accessing global memory is significantly slower than accessing shared memory44. Therefore, we divide global memory data into blocks which are copied into shared memory. Parallel reduction is performed within each block using shared memory to compute the \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
